{
  "id": "helix-graphite",
  "title": "Add Graphite stacking configuration for PR management",
  "category": "infrastructure",
  "description": "Configure Graphite CLI for stack-aware PR management to support the dev→staging→main promotion flow.\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Verify Graphite CLI is installed globally or document installation in CONTRIBUTING.md\n2. Initialize Graphite in the repo: `gt init`\n3. Track the main, staging, and dev branches in Graphite trunk config\n4. Add `.graphite_config` or update the existing config if present\n5. Add `docs/graphite-workflow.md` with usage instructions for stacked PRs\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Graphite config exists in the repo\n- `gt log short` shows the correct trunk\n- Workflow documentation covers: creating feature branches, submitting PRs, updating stacks",
